    {
      "id": "00320eab157abd04cdfac0c7e15193b35fbda7bc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-07-15 11:47:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: No score\n\nChris: bz 22281 was created exactly for you to designate something like -1chaos in your version with the --downstream-release configure switch.\n\nI agree however with the code that (now) warns of the mismatch, you will always see that warning if your tags have the -1chaos in them also.\n\nThere is some code in that check to strip _RC* off of the end of a tag and I'm about to extend that to (-|_)(WC|wc)[0-9] but seeing your use case here makes me wonder if we shouldn't just be more general here and strip of -*.\n\nIn any case, the code is also being changed to only look at the v* tags, so as long as you are happy to use only x.y.z-* tags and not create v* tags, you shouldn't get this warning.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "23902154f0ef7eb3c1c983a381485a4748d6301c",
