    {
      "id": "92eb587d27123db8f75e1b06552c5c63bb57616a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2011-07-19 17:10:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nBrian,\n\nI am not sure what you are getting at with this first sentence:\n\n\"Chris: bz 22281 was created exactly for you to designate something like -1chaos in your version with the --downstream-release configure switch.\"\n\nI am, of course, quite aware of that change.  Like you said, it was created for us, and we are using it.  But that doesn't change the fact that we also need to tag our releases in git.\n\nIn fact, the tag is what our automated build scripts use to feed the \"--downstream-release\" switch in our CHAOS build farm.  We just give the builder a URL and a tag.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
